theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A →
      closure (A : Set X) = closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
  intro hP1
  -- First inclusion: `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have h₁ :
      closure (A : Set X) ⊆
        closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
    have hSub :
        (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) :=
      Topology.P1_implies_subset_closure_interior_closure
        (X := X) (A := A) hP1
    exact closure_mono hSub
  -- Second inclusion: `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`.
  have h₂ :
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆
        closure (A : Set X) :=
    Topology.closure_interior_closure_subset_closure
      (X := X) (A := A)
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem isOpen_union_interiors {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    IsOpen ((interior (A : Set X)) ∪ interior (B : Set X)) := by
  -- Both `interior A` and `interior B` are open sets.
  have hA : IsOpen (interior (A : Set X)) := isOpen_interior
  have hB : IsOpen (interior (B : Set X)) := isOpen_interior
  -- The union of two open sets is open.
  exact hA.union hB
